<h1> The Present tense in Portuguese </h1>

<h3> The present tense in Portuguese follows some basic rules, however, be careful when using as some verys are irregular! </h3>

<p> The present tense is used to descibe actions that are happening now, in the present e.g. </p>
<p> I go to the shop </p>
<p> Eu vou Ã  loja </p>

